Review Text: This Wetherspoon pub is just like any other in the franchise, offering the same familiar experience. The main difference is that this location might be slightly smaller than usual. However, what sets this place apart is the fantastic prices. I was able to enjoy a full English breakfast for an incredible ¬£2.99, and I doubt anyone can beat that value. If you're looking for a budget-friendly meal without compromising on taste, this Wetherspoon pub is a great choice. The wide selection of food and drinks at such affordable prices make it a go-to spot for a satisfying meal.

Delightful place with a good atmosphere. The food was good and affordable. A lot of variety of it as well. Had a dinner of fish and chips, it was really good and tasty. Also a recommended place to hang out and have a meal together. Definitely will come back again.

Well. Where to start. So, the place looks nice inside. Dark, presumably so you can't see too closely.
The nuggets where surprisingly very tasty, the burger has tiny and dry. We shared the loaded fries, they could have been better, the cheese was barely melted and lacked flavour. The halloumi was a bit overdone but was also quite cold on arrival.
Staff seemed quite nice, although rushed.
The place was letdown by the stereotypical spoons crowd.
People pushing in, arguing with each other and a delightful couple who seemed close to good old fisticuffs. That might be your type of thing, but not mine.
Always pleasant helpful staff. Clean tables. Great place for breakfast or dinner. You know what you are getting at a decent price

Lovely place, was in yesterday and ordered an 8oz steak, with chips, onion rings, peas and a pepsi for just over ¬£13.

The chips were the best I have ever had, very large and substantial.

Really enjoyed the steak and the waitress was lovely.

If I'm around that area again, I think I'll be going back for another steak.
Recommended Dishes: Chips, Steak with Peppercorn Sauce Bernaise

Review Text: What an absolute delight it was to stop off here on the off chance to then be greeted by beautiful attentive staff, in a classically decorated modern bar. Drinks so reasonably priced but the melt in the mouth, medium rare steak with fluffy thick cut chips topped with a homemade pepper corn sauce. It's a basic meal made exceptionally by the way its prepared. I've eaten some expensive steaks but for somewhere you would think is run of the mill, taking the chance you won't be disappointed. After a morning of shear running around to be pleasantly satisfied with the simplicity of decent well cooked standard food has made my week. I would recommend this venue to anyone looking for no fuss but inviting environment with great staff and above standard food. Thank you guys an girls.
Had breakfast.  Value for money.  Excellent atmosphere.  Very good ambience.  I wonder how they manage to serve such excellent fare at such prices.  Their lemonade is recommended.

Seriously. Why bother. Farce

Meant to be fish & chips incase you are wondering, the yellow thing twice the size of a pepper sachet was the fish
Nice restaurant. Many kinds od Beer. Meals were very good. If i will travel again to Manchester, will go there again.

very good, love their large portion vegetarian full English breakfast and bottomless refillable hot drinks! all for just ¬£4! (breakfast ¬£3, bottomless refillable hot drink ¬£1) such good value for money! should come and definitely recommended üëçüèº
This is my favourite Wetherspoons in Manchester. Got rowdy the last visit. But it wasn't annoying because the pub is quite spacious.
Recommended Dishes: Freshly Battered Fish and Chips, Beef Burger, Chocolate Brownie, Chips, Burger

Review Text: Great selection of food and drinks. Hannah is an asset to the company - all of the food that she prepared was exquisite for the price. I will definitely be frequenting this pub.
I really like this bar, especially the atmosphere and mostly beer
A nice and spacious pub with sports on TV for those who are into that. Bar staff and fairly quick and friendly. Food options are okay. It is a nice place for groups to just chill out and chat though.

I really like this wetherspoons. I come in here every so often to take advantage of the deals as spending ¬£4 on a hot meal and drink is far better than spending ¬£3.40 on a meal deal in Tesco's. The staff are wonderful and most of the people who are here during the day and weekday evenings are wonderful.

OMG! Fabulous!
I am just beside myself, food was evenly warm (top marks to chef microwave).
Black grape AU vodka with cranberry juice is amazing - knocked me out instantly
You know a pub is good when your shoes stick to the floor
Top Notch.

Nice and friendly place. Staff are excellent and are exceedingly attentive.
A very reasonably priced establishment for food and drink.
Warm and cosy with a few characters frequenting the bar.
Good for solo or group visits and an outside area for the smoker and people who just like to sit outside with a drink and watch the world go by.
Downside is that there is no nearby parking or WiFi available.
Great calm pub with a cozy atmosphere where the food and attention is great. Amazing place to do some studying while having great food. Definitely recommend.
Well priced, decent foods. Had the chicken jalfrezi which came with rice, naan and 2 poppadoms.  Come in here when visiting daughter at uni, very convenient.
Great variety of drinks and the food was exceptional. I‚Äôve never had better customer service. I could tell that the preparation of the food handled by Hannah was sublime.
I love Ford Maddox , staff are Very Nice and polite , the food is always good and i always have a good crack in there xx

Best weatherspoons in Manchester . Even better than the gateway
3.99 mixed grill special was exceptional.
Good atmosphere better beer than the awful big hands the filthy little pub next to the academy. If your going to a gig go here .

Very bad experience over here at this place.. really bad service exhibited by the staff who served us( don't know the name). She was not nicee and not really fit for this particular job as this involves hospitality and I don't think she knows what that is. I wish we had gone to oodles and noodles which is right next to this place, instead of here - The service there  is just so amazing .. regret coming here.
Food was really good with excellent service. Place was clean and tidy

Quite surprised with the steak!

Good overall. Queit friendly place to eat with good prices. I had the simple steak (steak and chips) you get a drink within the price I had a coffee (Free refills), the steak and drink was only ¬£10.60. Ordered the steak Meduim rare it came more rare but I don't mind it that way. I was suprised because the steak was actually really good quality and tasted really nice very good meal for the price I would recommend the steak.

It's a Whetherspoons. What more can I say? Apart from unusually, you don't have to walk miles, go down into the basement, or climb through the back of a wardrobe to get to the loos.

Personally, I wouldn't choose to go to a Whetherspoons, but it was a colleague's leaving drinks.

Whilst I‚Äôm sure you can fault Wetherspoons for many things, you really cannot beat it on price. With many pints on offer for ~¬£2 and plenty of dinners for ~¬£5, ‚Äòspoons will always be a safe option. Decent service, plenty of seating, tables reliable sticky

It's just a spoons, you know what you're getting. Not the worst but not the best ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è. Visited purely for the convenience, food was alright but everytime I got a mixed grill it was different ü§£ ‚Ä¶
Great mix of people, not dominated by one demographic or socio-economic group. Real ales kept well, great value for money.
We like this place .amazing staff .fab service .great choice if ales . Love sitting out the front watching all the characters  going by
Good pub! Food was slightly greasy, but otherwise a good establishment!
I really enjoy my pint of Leffe here. Yes Leffe! On draught. Served in a chalice. Chilled. Outstanding. Good bar staff. Great service and unbelievable value for money. Keep it up folks. üëç ‚Ä¶
Just at the end of the curry mile and what a great pub and fantastic chilled feel about it, the food was amazing one of the best pizzas i have tasted. Great food and beer, friendly staff.

I visited your pub and was appalled by the service demonstrated by the manger on duty.

We ordered our food around 6:10pm and was told by our server that there was a 25 minute wait on food which was fine. We had a gig to go to for 7pm but didn‚Äôt mind being a little late.

After waiting 40 minutes and no sign of our food I decided to try to find out how long it would be. I asked the manager on duty who was serving drinks behind the bar. Before I could say anything he rudely said ‚ÄòIf you want to know how long your food will be there is a 30 minute wait on food. I told him but ours was over 40 minutes and he abruptly chimed in with ‚ÄòI said at LEAST 30 minutes.‚Äô I said can you find out how long it will take and his response was No all he can see is the information on the screen. I asked if he couldn‚Äôt just go and speak to the kitchen to find out as all I wanted was a rough eta. He then rudely went ‚ÄòFine‚Äô. After returning  his responses was ‚ÄòAbout 5 minutes could be less could be more‚Äô.

Our food arrived about 2 minutes later. I did have to return with my burger as there was no tennesse sauce with it. We ate the food which was Luke warm at best but after the unhelpful manner from the manager we didn‚Äôt bother complaining as we lost all faith in him.

Please could you respond with what action will be taken to make sure customers aren‚Äôt treated so rudely.

On a positive the lady that served me was pleasant and apologetic and had great customer service skills
The food is really good, the drinks as well and the place is very nice. The perfect place for a night out with friends.
This is a nice pub.  Friendly staff.  The food came out quick and was delicious
I ordered breakfast. Never received said breakfast and when I asked the manager he refused to assist me in any meaningful way also refusing to give me a refund
Hannah Rossiter makes this place well worth the 5 stars, she lights up the Ford Maddox brown (FMB) with her service and professionallism

Food was really poor , all meal just warm, Chicken üçó were smaller than a little finger and as wide as a little finger. We didn't even eat our food it was that poor. I won't be visiting this place any time soon nor will there be any meeting point. ‚Ä¶

AMAZING dark place. If I could give one piece of advice dim the lights even more as my eyes felt slightly irritated by the window. Chef did a grand job even let me add my own toppings to the pizza with a mayo base. Definitely will be coming back here. Perfect date night.
Had a great coffee here. Friendly staff. WiFi was not working

My partner and I regularly visit on a Sunday morning for breakfast.  I can thoroughly recommend the traditional breakfast, it is fresh, tasty and not greasy at all. The coffee is also top notch (Franke A800 coffee machine).  Arrive before 10.30am for breakfast as it does start to get a little busy. The Ford Maddox is also great in the evening.
Food is bad...for spoons...so bad. Pint of Coors tasted like line cleaner...not good...
Had a nice, cheap meal! Step free and the accessible bathroom was clean and spacious (I'm a wheelchair user). The bar is pretty high, but I could use the app to order!
Dropped in for a couple of drinks before heading to our hotel. Good ales and good service. Thanks.
Fantastic experience at Ford Madox Wetherspoons. Friendly staff, delicious food, and a lively atmosphere! üëçüèº
Recommended Dishes: Chicken Wings, Chips, Burger, Style Pancakes

Review Text: Great for drinks and people watching. Has cheap food that comes quick! Friendly staff

Nice food.. good menu good selection of beers wines and spirits... a great place for nhs employees with an added discount...
Update!
Staff don't like loud music
They think they are SAS.
One of them was lucky they didn't end up with a black eye for the way we was spoken to.
I hope Tim Martin reads his reviews.

I personally didn‚Äôt have a pleasant experience as the customer service was very poor .I really regret going there to celebrate a happy moment . My happy moment was turned out to be a disaster ‚òπÔ∏è
A Wetherspoons and a midweek visit. Clean roomy, as always good value food.
Not bad breakfast, service could do with a smile and customer friendly, but last last visit license act sign out of date, which overall needs some improvement.
Recommended Dishes: Freshly Battered Fish and Chips, American Breakfast, Burger

Review Text: It's another Wettherspoon's, pretty much like any other. Staff are friendly and helpful. Only criticism is that they had no dark ales, not even bottled.

Pretty good Wetherspoons, decent prices and quite nice inside as far as they go. Fast service and not extremely busy. Went with a friend and for cheap pitchers and very cheap pints, can't comment on the food, However some other people around us got some and it seemed nice enough.

They would rather put glasses on the shelves here, leaving a customer waiting at the bar seems normal pratice. Self absorbed staff and Olivia the Manager hasn't a clue about hospitality or customer service. Dreadful experience üò™ This place is not doing wetherspoons proud at all. Regular spoons attendee btw, and work a bar myself. Shockingly bad. If you don't care about how your treated as a paying customer, you should go here. üëéüèª
We visit as close to work and also doesn't tend to get too busy or noisy like the city ones get, so great for those who want to escape the maddness of the city.

Just a bog standard Spoon's
Reasonable priced .

The ambience is amazing, if you're looking for a place to hangout with your friends, pal around or even go on a date, this is the bar for you. The waiting staff are polite and efficient, and although I didn't sample the food, they did look amazing as the orders went out to the other tables. They have these book shelves in the pub too, if you fancy a read üòÅ. I would highly recommend going to this bar, if you find yourself on that side of town.

Lovely cosy atmosphere. BUT! Do not order Vegan Veggie Roasted Pizza! It was the worst pizza I've ever eaten. This is not the first time I order this pizza in a wetherspoon. Obviously, this disaster is very much related to the chef. So, my recommendation is just have some beer
Fantastic staff & really good atmosphere. One of the cheapest Wetherspoons in Manchester üëç ‚Ä¶
Great Food, served very quickly. Unusually quiet when I went which was around 12:00 on a Monday. Good Bathrooms which are clean.
Service could be faster, nice selection of grumpy customers but the topless bar staff are a bonus. And the free beer, every 3rd pint free. Love it. Duty staff excellent,never stop,
Amazing food, super incredibly nice staff and overall really good!!

The place hosts a nice, historic themed decor very wooden. One may say gothic slightly. The staff are 50/50, you get a smile from some and not so much from the others.

The beverages of this establishment are that of JD Wetherspoon's menu. Food too. The drinks have always been great  with no issues from my times there.

Very clean too.
Great place to meet friends and have a few cheap drinks.
Brilliant staff! They pulled out all the stops to serve us food quickly when we were hungry. Pleasant and helpful staff and a lovely place.
Lovely ambience...But be mindful that you won't have any mob. network inside so ensure to keep your mob. connected to their free WiFi.

Popular with students here , I mean it is literally under a huge student digs - and they have great prices, especially on a Monday where all drinks are very reduced. There‚Äôs a proper nice seat by the fireplace if you need to warm up. A nice layout and a decent outside bit on the road. This is my favourite Wetherspoons in Manchester I think.!!!
Love how dark it is in here proper crypt vibes... spooky! Would it be possible for me to meet one of the kitchen staff, Matthew "Orange Peel" Dix-Baker, his secret menu item is delectable.

This place has been a lifesaver for me recently as the coffee refill has kept me from starving!  I had a small English breakfast the other day and not only was it served with speed and efficiency but I enjoyed everything immensely.
Had a great night, a nice place for a catch up with friends
Excellent management.  I had an issue w my meal and he sorted it quickly and happily. Really appreciate it!
Exceptional service and the food really is quite good. Very similar to other Wetherspoons but that is expected. Solid location.

I work away from  home and pop in to spoons dor a cheap steak now and again. And honestly say this spoons is one of the best I've been to for a steak we had the gourmet sirloin and it wasn't like a usual spoons steak it was lean with no grizle running through the middle. The chef cooked it perfect, medium rare. Usually the spoons chef just cook all of them the same but this one can actually cook a steak properly.

Very homely pub with a large food and drink menu. Well managed, clean tables and toilets. Food and drinks served very quickly. Prices are very good and there's always some good discounts on something. Sometimes there can be mistakes with orders and payment.

We are exceedingly fond of this 'spoons establishment, and we believe it has the most superior carpet of all spoons ever (in our experience), but it could possibly perhaps be vacummed with higher frequency to reveal its true glory. Our further additional suggestions include the following:
- it is 14:23 on Thursday 14th November in the year MMIXX, and there is an outrageous deficiency of Christmas tree.
- mayonnaise on table 21, which resides adjacent to the portrait of our dear friend Konstantin on the righthand side, just before Satan's slot machines, requires an excess of upheavel to release the good stuff within - our dear friend Ezkaban suffered a terrible injury, but fortunately the hospital was in close proximity to the 'spoons.
- tinsel???
We will be back, tbc
I seen some crack heads trying to batter each other the other day out front. Top quality entertainment.

The lights in here make for a very unpleasant experience. Spot lights seem to be ideally places to keep the establishment dimly light but to face directly into your eyes no matter which way you look. Usual weatherspoons, huge bar, no one behind it, wait an age to be served
This is the best place I have ever been. Would highly recommend the coffee mayo.
Manager and workers seemed stook up and refused us drinks based on overlying the actual laws of only we could do that without getting in trouble.
Very nice Stella and manager specials x

Went on a Friday evening and Saturday morning after a gig. Polite staff, good service speed on the Saturday but Friday was a little slow. I can understand that it was busy but one set of drinks took around half an hour. I also got 3 small plates, and so did my friend - two of the plates were great, but my halloumi fries were overcooked and my friends were massively undercooked. I can't fault the place otherwise, it was one of the best Wetherspoons I've been to. Sets a good standard.

A strange one, we went in on a Sunday afternoon expecting the usual bustling Wetherspoons but it was half empty.  Probably because, as we later found  out, the fryers had broken down so only offering a very limited menu.  Friendly enough staff.  We'll try it out again when we're back on the area.
Food great, really nice cosy place, not too loud.
Party of 6 adults. Evening meal and drinks prior to a show nearby
I'll definitely come back again and again soon.

When we visited during Covid there were no [beef] steaks on steak night!

Went yesterday and there were. Nice steaks and mixed grill, wide selection of ales (but no Abbot), good service.

Not overly busy as most students are revising for exams.

Check the arithmetic if ordering on their app' though!

Update 220922

App seems sorted. Rather limited range of ales, but mixed grill as manager's special at ¬£4, so two ordered and very well cheffed. Super chips. Nearly ***** except till overcharged 5% for a bottle of wine compared with the card and the bar person couldn't sort it. In view of the huge discount on the food, I sucked it up

My family and I including two disabled pensioners went here to have a few drinks and something to eat, while we were there a fight broke out at a table amongst a group of men entirely nothing to do with us they carried on fighting outside despite this they were allowed back in unbelievably our table was then told to leave saying we were too noisy even though we weren‚Äôt when we tried to speak to the manager  Ryan he was quite frankly rude and insulting he clearly has no idea how to do his job  but this place does seem to have a reputation for this kind of thing personally I would avoid this place as there are plenty of places that serve better food and Their paying customers with decency and respect

Very spacious place with a massive seating area. Food is a bit hit and miss but in general good, exactly what you want from this chain. Refillable coffee is a nice touch. Gotta say the range of food and drink on offer is great though!
Gr8 service worth a visit prices spot on

This is a Wetherapoons with a nice charm.  Of course, you know what you're getting from a Spoons. You get a decent breakfast for cheap and unlimited coffee for a pound. After a night out, this is the place you wanna be to replemish in the morning. At this location, the food was served incredibly quick and you have unlimited access to the coffee machine. Aside from brektis, they have a lovely selection of ales and beers. This place is a great addition to the curry strip! Head on down and get the BIG full English and try finish it. Cheers!

It's a Wetherspoons pub on a single floor. Good wheelchair and walking-impaired acces. Staff are great, food is cooked to spec, service is generally swift, cleanliness is good. No complaints. Its my Go-To pub on Oxford Road in Manchester.
Very friendly and helpful staff! Excellent food and drinks!

Very friendly pub, seems to be well run. Good food, quickly served. Management seem to be good at handling issues.
Has to be said though, that the gents loos aren't well maintained. Locks hanging off, urinals leaking etc.
Still better than your average pub, but generally I expect better from a 'Spoons pub
Lots of off beer and plenty more that is going off.  Have had pints served to me here that made me choke it back up as it was completely rancid. Really bad cellar management I guess.

Happened on 28/09 at 09:30am

The food was good but the waitress wearing the black shirt was rude and careless.

She said in a rude tone: "can you stop raising your hand to call me"?

1. It's my culture.
2. It's no harm.
3. It's better than raising my voice in the current covid-situation.

My friend was served a coffee and after waiting for over 20 mins we were informed that it was self-service (which the waitress never mentioned before)..

I repeat, the food quality was very good but the customer service was terrible. Lack of care, ethics and culture awareness.

Good pub. Lovely food but the pub is spoilt by one of the Duty Managers Sharon. I have seen and heard her being very rude and agggressive to customers more than once.  She needs to be sent on a Customer Services course. She lets the pub down

I could call it my hobby: visiting spoons. This one is quite nice. We had a veggie breakfast here and it was decent. The place seemed clean, the toilets were alright. The close proximity to student accomodations indicate that one should expect hordes of youngsters at times but I'm alright with that!

I a full year and half in this pub in 2017 2018 and it was life line to us as our son was in hospital,  the place was buzzing and the staff were great , what's going on now , I know all about covid and the restrictions but now your open , like you have shouted about doing , you would think your staff would be greatfull to be at work , but today they couldn't care less it seems about anything. I'm very disappointed and I won't be rushing back anytime soon .Not a happy punter üò§

One of the cleanest Spoons I've ever been to, if not the cleanest. Service was quick, staff were polite. Food was definitely above par compared to other Spoons pubs, really big portions that were actually very well presented.
Decent wetherspoons, plenty of seating and clean. Food and drinks were excellent and the staff were friendly, would visit again !

Great place! Love coming with university friends here for cheap quality food. Lots of places inside, usually can manage to find one. The breakfast is also good, it's really nice and quiet to come in the morning. Stuff is friendly and serves fast. One of the favorite places to go.

Nice Spoons just up from the Curry Mile. We've met there a couple of times before going for a meal down the road. Good selection of beers, nice surroundings. A bit studenty, given the area. What's not to like?

Ok for quick drink. Food was nice. Advertised drinks unavailable. Whilst sat eating a man approached us asking for money. I always help homeless people out but don't think the staff should be allowing people to walk around asking people for money whilst they are sat eating. He then circulated around the place asking everyone.

As every wetherspoons this place has unbeatable prices for a remarkable food and beer list.

They have a good selection of hamburgers, pub classics and grills. The beer selection is excellent specially taking on account that all the pints are under 3¬£.

The only problem about this place is that in the bottom part of the local the smell of the bathroom air freshener is perceptible, but anyway there's plenty of room to take any other table

Very relaxed and pleasant place. I took my two boys to eat. The food was ok. Had a lovely time. Seemed to be a few families as well as students and older people.
Staff very good and obviously prices very cheap on food and alcohol.

Bit difficult to park around there.

It's a Wetherspoons and this one is typical of the breed. Mixed crowd from the rowdy to the more relaxed. My visit was for Sunday breakfast. Basic low cost food but some slightly more unusual items on the menu for the more adventurous, smashed avocado bagel for example. Facility to order and pay at table via App is great. Free hot drink refills welcomed.

Incredibly rude and ignorant staff, was served by two women tonight who treated us as if we were a burden or annoyance. Utterly disappointed with the customer service and attitude of staff. Would not recommend attending this Wetherspoons at all.

As usual with a Wetherspoons pub, the prices are outstanding. The guest ales in particular are very reasonably price with a varied selection. We ordered a fried chicken burger which was delicious, however the chips served with it were cold and undercooked. We let our waitress know and she took them away and replaced them with a larger serving, this time hot and perfectly cooked. As per, the decor left something to be desired but again the colour of the carpet is not a reason to visit a Wetherspoons.
The food is not first class, nearly all microwave and a lot is sent back üîô ‚Ä¶
Not been for a while.but it was fine meal was good appreciation the fact you could get smaller plates will go again
A good spoons. Does get busy during peak times but food is served quickly. Staff are polite. When the weather is cold, they often have a fire going inside which keeps it pretty cozy.

Now I do like to visit the odd Spoons but today's wasn't one of the gooduns. A very busy pub but looks due for a good clean and a bit more regular table clearing as I had to clear one for myself. But 5* for the really good service at the bar.
Quite a nice experience. Feel lovely and cosy on a nice winter night when ya looking for a pint to warm you through. Summer though, sit out and have a cig and a beer and just enjoy yourself :)
Went to order a meal and drink at the bar this afternoon, bar lady decided to ignore me and keep serving customers who came to the bar after me, so I took my custom elsewhere

Chose to eat here as usually wetherspoons are reliably decent food and service. Quiet when we arrived, had to clean our table as although no plates or cutlery etc on the table, the table was very dirty - lots of crumbs and dried out ketchup that needed scrubbing off. Ordered food which arrived just warm, and with food missing (2 sausages rather than 3 for sausage, chips and beans). When this was brought to the attention of the barman it was met with eye rolling, although it was rectified. When the meal was returned with the correct number of sausages the plate was just plonked down with no apology for the additional wait. Basically we were made to feel like we were being totally unreasonable by expecting what we'd ordered.  Don't think we'll be going back.

This bar is very friendly and well located. I strongly suggest you order the American style pancakes. It has WiFi and screens to watch sports. It is inexpensive compared to other pubs. Beers are ¬£3 and up.

Decent prices, busy though, and part of order not delivered after ordering on the app. After enquiry, it took another ten minutes for the drink to arrive. When they're busy they are slow with service so just keep that in mind.
Wonderful place to dine with your friends.
Recommended Dishes: Freshly Battered Fish and Chips, Beef Burger, American Breakfast, Chips, Burger, Steak with Peppercorn Sauce Bernaise, Mixed Grill Platter

Review Text: This was my 4th time visiting and I have always enjoyed a cozy meal with friends here. I had rated this place 5/5 last time I visited but this time I rated it 4/5. There are two reasons. First, the internet reception is really poor if you are sitting on a table in the internal area. You can't order food through the wetherspoon app. Even the WiFi didn't help. This might be a temporary issue but it was an off point. Second, I'm a fan of their food+drink discounted offer but I feel they can add more variety of soft drinks and alcoholic drinks in the offer. Just some temporary suggestions, I'd love to update the review the next time I visit!
Love the place. It's a great local with a city feel to it. Can't fault it. Good staff, cheap beer and food always good. This is high praise as I'm not the easiest pleased!
Took 45 minutes to get served. The bar was poorly managed.
Went here for a hangover breakfast is awesome. Nice low lighting, free refills on coffee. All day brunch. Its a w Wetherspoons so you know what you're getting but I really enjoyed myself

Food is a hit and miss, and occasionally the staff can be slightly rude. One time me and a couple friends bought a lot of food and drinks and our custom was rewarded with ‚Äúyou‚Äôve been here for hours, I think it‚Äôs time for you to leave now‚Äù which I find extremely appalling considering th amount of money we spent on that day as well as other days as it‚Äôs somewhat our local. Obviously the drinks are cheap and food relatively cheap but on the curry mile there‚Äôs much nicer food for less money and with a Lidl right next to it I‚Äôd say if possible just find a base and get some Lidl drinks and actually nice food from the curry mile.

Good food, open fire and a few chapters of a book.  My daughter was in hospital over Christmas and new year with pneumonia. I needed a place warm, change of seen. Excellent and much needed. An not expensive xxx
Good food, cheap and fast. Amazing

Can get busy in term time as the university accommodation is very close. The food is good and there's a wide range of beers. The main pub area is very big but as its on a main road in Manchester the beer garden is simply chairs and tables on the wide pavement

Amazing service, great food. Was served my food order less than 8 minutes after ordering! Clean and well organised. The blonde waitress is awesome, give her a raise! Better service than a Michelin star establishment!!
Took some work mates in for breakfast. The menu was reduced, food was cold, and in part burnt. Cheap enough though
This used to be a great establishment, but due to frequent instances of opening later than designated time, I have had to take my custom elsewhere
The food was abysmal, service was slow. Staff were lovely, but conditions for them aren't great. Drink and eat elsewhere.
Staff are always friendly, impressed with covid precautions

It was very busy when we came to this place, so there was limited space and it was a bit too noisy to talk, so perhaps not the ideal choice of venue, but despite the business we got great fast service and the cocktails weren't too expensive either. Recommended if you like a rowdy place for drinks.
Usual Weatherspoons. Very busy. The breakfast was ok. The poor lass doing tables and bringing out the food was run of her feet. Think they could.do with some extra staff
